<a:ObjectID>F69B9159-941A-4C13-8E6B-46D9E9C9CE84</a:ObjectID>
<a:Name>REFERENCES</a:Name>
<a:Code>REFERENCES</a:Code>
<a:CreationDate>880027320</a:CreationDate>
<a:Creator>OME08</a:Creator>
<a:ModificationDate>1681393914</a:ModificationDate>
<a:Modifier>U008131</a:Modifier>
<a:Comment>The RFR Data-Model mainly consists in the different data sets managed within the References Functional Domain : countries, currencies, banalised codifications, main codifications, transaction codes, organisation (subsidiaries, Units)...

It also includes data for the Security Functional Domain (Users, Security) and misc. other more technical elements.

It now also supports the configuration of Dynamic Conditions and misc config data for the One GL system.</a:Comment>
