<o:Table Id="o633">
<a:ObjectID>6858CE2D-5CC2-423B-84FA-DA1579E22B9F</a:ObjectID>
<a:Name>Direction table</a:Name>
<a:Code>TDIR</a:Code>
<a:CreationDate>880027320</a:CreationDate>
<a:Creator>OME08</a:Creator>
<a:ModificationDate>1318428409</a:ModificationDate>
<a:Modifier>OME08</a:Modifier>
<a:Comment>Table des directions</a:Comment>
<a:TotalSavingCurrency/>
<a:Description>{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.21.2509;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 This table contains the list of directions of a SCOR subsidiary. This is the first level of the hierarchical model of organization (leadership belongs to an affiliated company and contains sub-branches that it contains the same units).\par
\par
Reminder: in Omega, a subsidiary is modeled by:\par
\par
   - Directions\par
   - Sub-Directions\par
   - Units\par
\par
Hierarchical Description of SCOR Organisation in Omega :\par
Level 0 = \tab Subsidiary\tab #01\par
Level 1 =\tab &quot;Direction&quot;\tab #01 - 01\par
Level 2 = \tab &quot;Sub-Direction&quot;\tab #01 - 011 (complement of Direction number),\par
Level 3 =\tab &quot;Unit&quot;\tab\tab #01 - 0111 (complement of Sub-Direction number).\par
\par
Accounting Establishment by Subsidiary (# Madrid for SCOR R\&#39;e9). Doesn&#39;t enter in the hierarchical description.\par
\par
Users are attached to 1 principal Unit (several if given)  -&gt; Authorizations on parts of the Data.\par
\par
Each Subsidiary has to define it&#39;s own Organization in Omega.\par
}
</a:Description>
<c:Columns>
