<o:Table Id="o727">
<a:ObjectID>A0185A05-6004-432D-BA35-7BA4EE818BA0</a:ObjectID>
<a:Name>Nahn parameters table</a:Name>
<a:Code>TNAHNPAR</a:Code>
<a:CreationDate>880027320</a:CreationDate>
<a:Creator>OME08</a:Creator>
<a:ModificationDate>1318503840</a:ModificationDate>
<a:Modifier>OME08</a:Modifier>
<a:Comment>Table des paramètres NAHN</a:Comment>
<a:TotalSavingCurrency/>
<a:Annotation>{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.21.2509;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 Table of parameters detection of extraordinary business on Underwriting Treaty.\par
\par
Extraordinary business are first detected on over-capacity underwriting (in TUWCAP), but also (treated only) on combinations of underwriting criteria, among LoB, SoB, ToP, Territory Risk, Warranty, Great Nature .\par
\par
This table also serves to set the possible need to resort to technical advice for treaties on the same criteria.\par
\par
For these parameters, we do not manage history.\par
}
</a:Annotation>
<c:Columns>
<o:Column Id="o2248">
