<o:Table Id="o788">
<a:ObjectID>74D5FD5D-9E84-4DD1-AF24-8AC2E8FCCA3B</a:ObjectID>
<a:Name>Remote server List</a:Name>
<a:Code>TRPCSRV</a:Code>
<a:CreationDate>880027320</a:CreationDate>
<a:Creator>OME08</a:Creator>
<a:ModificationDate>1378731741</a:ModificationDate>
<a:Modifier>FRXB087</a:Modifier>
<a:Comment>Remote Server List for Worldwilde transaction</a:Comment>
<a:TotalSavingCurrency/>
<a:Description>{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.21.2509;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 This table contains three occurrences, corresponding to the servers database of three continental sites in Scor. These are the Sybase server that could be used for a transaction requiring a global information as FACT.\par
In the same transaction, you can then access the local server and remote server 2.\par
\par
In continental architecture at 3 sites, there are:\par
- Sites FRA1, SGP1, USA1\par
- The server name attached to the site\par
- The server status (active or inactive)\par
\par
This table allows remote configuration of seveur to have a transparent routing to remote servers.\par
It is used by the RPC procedure ptSvcRPC present in BTEC.\par
}
</a:Description>
<c:Columns>
<o:Column Id="o2288">
<a:ObjectID>FB4DA2EE-33E5-4832-9333-6C55D49EB7D8</a:ObjectID>
<a:Name>Production site</a:Name>
<a:Code>PRDSIT_CF</a:Code>
<a:CreationDate>880027320</a:CreationDate>
<a:Creator>OME08</a:Creator>
<a:ModificationDate>1378731741</a:ModificationDate>
<a:Modifier>FRXB087</a:Modifier>
<a:Comment>Continental production site</a:Comment>
<a:DataType>char(4)</a:DataType>
<a:Length>4</a:Length>
<a:Column.Mandatory>1</a:Column.Mandatory>
<a:AutoMigrated>1</a:AutoMigrated>
<a:Description>Site continentale de production

Sur la base de l&#39;architecture continentale à 3 sites, les valeurs peuvent être FRA1, USA1, SGP1</a:Description>
</o:Column>
<o:Column Id="o2289">
<a:ObjectID>9E67B920-C2D5-4314-9D21-5C5F7D872E99</a:ObjectID>
<a:Name>DataServer Name</a:Name>
<a:Code>SRVNME_CF</a:Code>
<a:CreationDate>880027320</a:CreationDate>
<a:Creator>OME08</a:Creator>
<a:ModificationDate>880027320</a:ModificationDate>
<a:Modifier>OME08</a:Modifier>
<a:Comment>Sybase dataserver</a:Comment>
<a:DataType>varchar (30)</a:DataType>
<a:Length>30</a:Length>
<a:Column.Mandatory>1</a:Column.Mandatory>
<a:Description>Nom du serveur de données rattaché au site de production</a:Description>
</o:Column>
<o:Column Id="o2290">
<a:ObjectID>4958376C-B4FE-4F0A-BE24-B5B56C92E666</a:ObjectID>
<a:Name>Server status</a:Name>
<a:Code>STATUS_B</a:Code>
<a:CreationDate>880027320</a:CreationDate>
<a:Creator>OME08</a:Creator>
<a:ModificationDate>880027320</a:ModificationDate>
<a:Modifier>OME08</a:Modifier>
<a:Comment>Server status (active or inactive)</a:Comment>
<a:DataType>bit</a:DataType>
<a:Column.Mandatory>1</a:Column.Mandatory>
<a:Description>Etat du site: Actif ou Inactif
Actif: 1
Inactif:0

Cela permet de désactiver dynamiquement un site de production temporairement.

Exemple d&#39;utilisation: Sur le serveur de développement Paris, on veut pouvoir travailler avec l&#39;application fac  sans que les accès remote soient désactivés.
Par conséquent,status_b sera à 0 pour les occurences des sites de production USA1 et SGP1</a:Description>
</o:Column>
</c:Columns>
