<o:Table Id="o635">
<a:ObjectID>4F63D708-FE85-4878-BE1E-9910D331BF9A</a:ObjectID>
<a:Name>Group table</a:Name>
<a:Code>TGRP</a:Code>
<a:CreationDate>880027320</a:CreationDate>
<a:Creator>OME08</a:Creator>
<a:ModificationDate>1326122106</a:ModificationDate>
<a:Modifier>OME08</a:Modifier>
<a:Comment>Table des groupes</a:Comment>
<a:TotalSavingCurrency/>
<a:Description>{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.21.2509;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1036\f0\fs20 This table contains the list of directions of a SCOR subsidiary. This is the first level of the hierarchical model of organization (leadership belongs to an affiliated company and contains sub-branches that it contains the same units).\par
\par
Reminder: in Omega, a subsidiary is modeled by:\par
\par
   - Directions\par
   - Sub-Directions\par
   - Units\lang1033\par
\par
Hierarchical Description of SCOR Organisation in Omega :\par
Level 0 = \tab Subsidiary\tab #01\par
Level 1 =\tab &quot;Direction&quot;\tab #01 - 01\par
Level 2 = \tab &quot;Sub-Direction&quot;\tab #01 - 011 (complement of Direction number),\par
Level 3 =\tab &quot;Unit&quot;\tab\tab #01 - 0111 (complement of Sub-Direction number).\par
\par
Accounting Establishment by Subsidiary (# Madrid for SCOR R\&#39;e9). Doesn&#39;t enter in the hierarchical description.\par
\par
Users are attached to 1 principal Unit (several if given)  -&gt; Authorizations on parts of the Data.\par
\par
Each Subsidiary has to define it&#39;s own Organization in Omega.\par
\par
2011-12-05 / Omega2\par
Added Division and Active unit indicator\par
}
</a:Description>
<a:Annotation>{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.21.2509;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 RFR - Booleans XXXGRP_B specify the types of different organizational groups of SCOR. They are exploited by the application to limit the list of user groups and control groups entering codes.\par
\par
This typology is established according to two dimensions:\par
\par
- The function (underwriting, policy administration, accounts, rules, claims)\par
- The category of contracts concerned (treated, FACS, retrocession).\par
\par
For example, the underwriting group of a treaty (window treatments) must be both an underwriting group (UWGRP = 1) and a treated group (TRTGRP = 1).\par
\par
the 7/5/03 :same for the column GEDGRP_B\par
}
</a:Annotation>
