<a:Name>Countries by Country Grouping</a:Name>
<a:Code>TCTYBGP</a:Code>
<a:CreationDate>880027320</a:CreationDate>
<a:Creator>OME08</a:Creator>
<a:ModificationDate>1326886887</a:ModificationDate>
<a:Modifier>OME08</a:Modifier>
<a:Comment>Association table to manage the set of Countries or Sub-Groupings belonging to a Country Grouping.
Depending on the Grouping type, sub-groupings may be included. Otherwise only Countries are included.</a:Comment>
<a:TotalSavingCurrency/>
<a:Description>{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.21.2509;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 This table contains the list of countries by country supra entities. A country can belong to one or more country supra entity.\par
\par
Country Supra entity types:\par
\par
Save value &quot;0&quot; for the country supra entities captured as &quot;exposure area&quot; (or market in the FACS vocabulary). These groups have not intersection, except for the &quot;world wide&quot;.\par
\par
Save value &quot;1&quot; for the FACS RISK AREAS\par
}
</a:Description>
