<o:Table Id="o716">
<a:ObjectID>406F3F43-ABA7-4756-AD5C-9C548DDBE04F</a:ObjectID>
<a:Name>Country or Country Grouping</a:Name>
<a:Code>TCTYSUP</a:Code>
<a:CreationDate>880027320</a:CreationDate>
<a:Creator>OME08</a:Creator>
<a:ModificationDate>1366031707</a:ModificationDate>
<a:Modifier>u000252</a:Modifier>
<a:Comment>Summary of all Countries and Country Grouping defined in the system
(all TSUPENT and TCTY records are duplicated in this table)</a:Comment>
<a:TotalSavingCurrency/>
<a:Annotation>{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.21.2509;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 RFR - Redundant table of countries and groupings (sup entities). A line-by-country or group.\par
\par
This table is the table of countries or country groupings. It contains the list of countries + country groupings type, indicationof the type of grouping. Applications may need to filter out of their need.\par
\par
Are planned:\par
\par
Save value &quot;0&quot; for the country groupings grasped as &quot;exposure area&quot; (or market in the vocabulary FACS). These groups have the characteristic of not to present intersection, except for the &quot;world wide&quot;.\par
\par
Save value &quot;1&quot; for RISK AREAS FACS. (and only them).\par
}
</a:Annotation>
<c:Columns>
<o:Column Id="o2841">
<a:ObjectID>E4EDB353-8852-4FB7-AEE1-4E7AD26E50FD</a:ObjectID>
