<o:Table Id="o757">
<a:ObjectID>E0F3E97F-E8D2-4398-A2E4-9627A583656B</a:ObjectID>
<a:Name>SERN Subzones</a:Name>
<a:Code>TSUBZONE</a:Code>
<a:CreationDate>880027320</a:CreationDate>
<a:Creator>OME08</a:Creator>
<a:ModificationDate>1327586964</a:ModificationDate>
<a:Modifier>OME08</a:Modifier>
<a:Comment>SERN disaster subzone definitions (based on CRETA zones)

A lot of fields are actually copies from the TCRESTAL table.
</a:Comment>
<a:TotalSavingCurrency/>
<a:Description>{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}{\f1\fnil Verdana;}{\f2\fnil\fcharset0 Verdana;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.21.2509;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1033\f0\fs20 2012-01-26 / Omege 2.0\par
\pard - \cf1\f1 TCR_CRESTA_CT\lang1036\f2  field removed (not present in the database)\cf0\f0\fs20\par
}
</a:Description>
<a:Annotation>{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.21.2509;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 Created on the 11/08/97 (sern).\par
\par
Redundant table of TCRESTAL for each sub zones (UPPCRESTA_CT not null in TCRESTAL).\par
\par
Update rules:\par
\par
TCRESTAL                                      TSUBZONE\par
CTY_CF                   =&gt;                     CTY_CF\par
UPPCRESTA_CT   =&gt;                     CRESTA_CT\par
                                                          SUBZONE_CF (char(3) )\par
CRESTAOFF_LS    =&gt;                      SUBZONE_LS      \par
CRESTA_LM           =&gt;                      SUBZONE_LM\par
CRESTA_CT           =&gt;                      CRESTANBR_CT (crossed reference TCRESTA (CTY_CT&amp;CRESTA_CT) et TSUBZONE (CTY_CF&amp;CRESTANBR_CT)\par
}
</a:Annotation>
