<o:Table Id="o702">
<a:ObjectID>1E70643A-74A2-41F2-AF4D-2B296A5221C7</a:ObjectID>
<a:Name>Banalised codes table</a:Name>
<a:Code>TBANAL</a:Code>
<a:CreationDate>880027320</a:CreationDate>
<a:Creator>OME08</a:Creator>
<a:ModificationDate>1323274433</a:ModificationDate>
<a:Modifier>OME08</a:Modifier>
<a:Comment>Table des codes banalisés fonctionnels</a:Comment>
<a:TotalSavingCurrency/>
<a:Description>{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.21.2509;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 2011-12-05 / Omega2\par
Added &quot;Group code indicator&quot;\fs20\par
}
</a:Description>
<a:Annotation>{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.21.2509;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 RFR - This table is administered by users, like the rest of the repository. A window will be provided for this purpose.\par
However, the list of column names given in this table will be initialized by the development teams. This list will be entered into the table TBANAL with associated labels in TBANALL. The name of the column used for this list is &quot;banalized  codification&quot; column values will be prefixed by the code of the user module on 2 characters followed by an order ID, the name of the column will be in the labels table (column COLVAL_LS), in French.\par
\par
Note: the module code indicates who is responsible for the creation of a codification. This codification, however, can be used later by other modules.\par
\par
Example :\par
\par
1.\tab Development team : Banalised code definition:\par
\par
TBANAL :\par
Column name = &quot;banalized code&quot;,\par
Column value = &quot;FA001&quot; (example if update by Fac module),\par
\par
Column name = &quot;banalized code&quot;,\par
Column value = &quot;FA002&quot; (example if update by Fac module),\par
\par
The table TBANALL will contain associated labels,in our example:\par
\par
French language,\par
Column name = &quot;banalized code&quot;,\par
Column value = &quot;FA001&quot;,\par
Short column label = &quot;commission type code&quot;,\par
\par
langue fran\&#39;e7ais,\par
Column name = &quot;banalized code&quot;,\par
Column value = &quot;FA002&quot;,\par
Short column label = &quot;deposit mode code&quot;,\par
.....\par
\par
2.\tab The data capture of banalized codification (codes + labels) is performed on a window of the Reference module. The user begins by selecting the column name to manage (&quot;Model Code Committee&quot; ..) and enter the corresponding codification:\par
\par
TBANAL :\par
\par
Column name = &quot;commission type code&quot;,\par
Column value  = &quot;1&quot;,\par
\par
Column name = &quot;commission type code&quot;,\par
Column value = &quot;2&quot;,\par
...\par
\par
Column name = &quot;deposit mode code&quot;,\par
Column value = &quot;1&quot;,\par
...\par
\par
The table TBANALL will contain associated labels,in our example :\par
\par
French language,\par
Column name = &quot;commission type code&quot;,\par
Column value  = &quot;1&quot;,\par
Short column label = &quot;fixed commission&quot;,\par
\par
French language,\par
Column name = &quot;commission type code&quot;,\par
Column value = &quot;2&quot;,\par
Short column label = &quot;variable commission&quot;,\par
\par
French language,\par
Column name = &quot;deposit mode code&quot;,\par
Column value = &quot;1&quot;,\par
Short column label  = &quot;cash&quot;,\par
.....\par
}
</a:Annotation>
