<o:Table Id="o764">
<a:ObjectID>075B799F-F66F-41C2-B4CC-385908E21C3E</a:ObjectID>
<a:Name>User Roles</a:Name>
<a:Code>TROLES</a:Code>
<a:CreationDate>880027320</a:CreationDate>
<a:Creator>OME08</a:Creator>
<a:ModificationDate>1326824543</a:ModificationDate>
<a:Modifier>OME08</a:Modifier>
<a:Comment>Association table between Users and Access Rights Profiles</a:Comment>
<a:TotalSavingCurrency/>
<a:Description>{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.21.2509;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 This table contains the list of jobs and their profiles associated with each application.\par
This combination of PROFILES &amp; JOBS is done subsidiary by subsidiary (the job and the profile must have the same subsidiary code).\par
\par
Table added the 7/10/97 to replace the table TROLE\par
\par
\lang1033 2012-01-17 / Omega 2.0\par
- Added the PRFSCOPE_CT and GLOBAL_B fields for Omega 2.0 Access Control\par
- Added PRF_CF as part of primary key --&gt; In Omega 2.0, a user may indeed have multiple roles for a Domain (one &quot;global&quot; and possibly multiple specific to sets of ledgers)\lang1036\par
}
</a:Description>
<a:Annotation>{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.21.2509;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 RFR - The table of roles allows to specify, for each user and each  Omega Application, what is the profile associated (ie all permits granted or not).\par
\par
This combination of PROFILES &amp; USER is done subsidiary by subsidiary (the trade and the profile must have the same code branch).\par
\par
\par
The table added on the 07/10/97 has to replace the table TROLE\par
}
</a:Annotation>
<c:Columns>
